Class AbstractDataReader<T extends AngstdData>

All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
XdomReader
public abstract class AbstractDataReader<T extends AngstdData>
extends java.lang.Object
implements DataReader<T>

Abstract class AbstractDataReader is the basic implementation for the DataReader interface. A Reader object is created from a file, string or stream which is passed to the abstract method getData(). This method must be implemented by a subclass and should be responsible for the actual parsing.

Because the return type of the methods are generic the requested type must implement the empty AngstdData interface.

Author:
Andreas Held
